📘 Day 4: Loops in Java ❗

🚀 `for` loop
🚀 `while` loop
🚀 `do-while` loop
🚀 `break` & `continue`


➡️ What are Loops?

Loops are used to execute a block of code repeatedly until a condition is met.

👉 They help in:   * Reducing code repetition
                   * Automating tasks
                   * Iterating over data


➡️ Types of Loops in Java

🔹 1. `for` Loop

Used when the number of iterations is known
Syntax:    for (initialization; condition; update)
               {
                    // code
               }


Example:     for (int i = 1; i <= 5; i++) 
                {
                    System.out.println(i);
                }

--------------------------------------------------------------------------------------

🔹 2. `while` Loop

Used when the number of iterations is not fixed
Syntax:      while (condition) 
              {
                // code
              }

Example:   int i = 1;
           while (i <= 5)
            {
              System.out.println(i);
              i++;
           }

--------------------------------------------------------------------------------------

🔹 3. `do-while` Loop

Executes the block at least once, even if condition is false
Syntax:     do 
              {
                // code
              }
            while (condition);


Example:    int i = 1;
            do
              {
                  System.out.println(i);
                  i++;
              }
            while (i <= 5);

--------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------

🔹 4. `break` Statement

Used to exit the loop immediately
Example:    for (int i = 1; i <= 5; i++)
            {
              if (i == 3) break;
              System.out.println(i);
            }

---------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------

🔹 5. `continue` Statement

Used to skip the current iteration
Example:    for (int i = 1; i <= 5; i++)
              {
               if (i == 3) continue;
               System.out.println(i);
              }

---------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------

🧠 Key Points
* `for` → when iterations are known
* `while` → condition-based loop
* `do-while` → runs at least once
* `break` → stops loop
* `continue` → skips iteration


🚀 Real-World Usage

Loops are used in:
* 🛒 Processing multiple items in billing systems
* 🏦 Transaction processing in banking
* 🎮 Game loops
* 📊 Data processing & reports



📌 Summary
* Loops help in efficient repetition of code
* Different loops serve different use cases
* `break` and `continue` control loop flow
* Essential for real-world programming

